<Rewrite PAsource="" >A KINKY killer </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >was jailed for life </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >yesterday for </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >murdering </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >a </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >74-year-old widow.
</Verbatim>

<Verbatim PAsource="" >Divorced father-of-three Kevin Morrison </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >knifed </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >Alice Rye </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >to death in </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >her home </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >on </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >the Wirral, Merseyside, </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >after torturing her to get bank </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >details</Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >.
</Rewrite>

<Rewrite PAsource="" >He pushed </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >knives </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >in the mum-</Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >of-three</Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >'s </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >eyes </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >to make it look like a </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >ritualistic killing </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >before stealing her </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >jewellery </Verbatim>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >and the knickers she was wearing.
</Verbatim>

<Verbatim PAsource="" >Morrison 60, formerly of Toole, Cheshire, </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >went </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >to police </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >and blamed another man for reward </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >money</Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >.
</Rewrite>

<Rewrite PAsource="" >But he was arrested after Mrs Rye's </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >knickers were found in </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >his </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >rented lock-up garage.
</Verbatim>

<Rewrite PAsource="" >Jailing him at </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >Liverpool Crown Court, Mr Justice Douglas Brown branded him a "truly evil man".
</Verbatim>


